        <p><img src="../Images/mlt_pxls.gif" width="10" height="20" hspace="0"><span class="headlines"> 
          <strong><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Press Releases</font></strong></span></p>
        <span class="news"> </span><!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="Text" --> 
              
              <p align="right" class="headlines"><br>
                SYSPRO Software Excels in Satisfaction Ratings in CTS Survey<span class="news"> <br>
                <font color="#FFFFFF"> <img src="../../Images/clear.gif" hspace="5" vspace="5" align="right"> 
                </font> 
                <br>
                </span><span class="headlinebody">December 17, 2002 – SYSPRO has announced that its manufacturing software scored exceptionally well in all key categories in the just released 2003 Edition of the CTS Manufacturing Software Survey: User Satisfaction Ratings for Leading PC-Based ERP Systems.  The CTS survey results were compiled from questionnaires sent to users of the industry-leading manufacturing software systems.  Survey questions were designed to “find out the general level of satisfaction with the products, implementation and whether user expectations were met with regard to various characteristics of the product.”<br>
 <br>
SYSPRO users returned approximately one-third of all questionnaires received by CTS and were by far the largest sample in the study.  Of these, 85% had been using SYSPRO manufacturing software for more than a year.    Ninety-five percent expressed satisfaction with their SYSPRO software systems.   More than 97.5% of the SYSPRO respondents said they were satisfied with the flexibility of their SYSPRO software, while more than 82% said the software had been fully implemented in less than six months.  Similarly, nearly 88% expressed satisfaction with the “time and cost of implementation,” with 95% of the SYSPRO sites reporting satisfaction with vendor support.  More than 87% of the SYSPRO respondents felt maintenance costs were as expected, while 33% noted they were less than anticipated, reflecting the SYSPRO approach to be a cost-effective, long-term solution for businesses.  On a weighted average rating system applied to all responses, SYSPRO earned the highest overall ranking, especially when also considering systems with 50 employees and above.<br>
<br>
The survey respondents represented a balance of small, medium and large manufacturers in Make to Order, Engineer to Order, Job Shop, Process and Mixed-Mode manufacturing environments.  SYSPRO also had the highest number of respondents in four of the five areas.  <br>
<br>
SYSPRO company officials expressed particular gratification at the exceptional rankings.  According to Vice President of US Marketing, Joey Benadretti, “The high rankings are welcome, but are really no surprise.  Our Customer Service Department continually polls users to determine their satisfaction and takes steps to remedy any who are in the least bit unhappy.   Similarly, we were not surprised by the excellent response on software implementation time.  The SYSPRO STARS Implementation Methodology is rapidly setting the industry standard.”  Benadretti was elated that the largest number of respondents was from SYSPRO sites.  “SYSPRO users are a passionate group,” he said.<br>
<br>
Benadretti went on to point out that SYSPRO retains a very strong relationship with both customers and channel partners, resulting in many of the desired features and functions available in its latest SYSPRO 6.0 software coming from these groups.<br>
<br>
CTS was founded in 1983 by Sheldon Needle, a nationally recognized expert in PC-based software.  CTS has offered software reviews and consulting services to an impressive roster of more than 18,000 customers worldwide.  CTS is based in Rockville, Md.<br>
<br>
SYSPRO is a world leader in providing manufacturing, distribution and financial accounting software solutions with thousands of installations in more than 50 countries.   In Q3/2002, the company released its newest software offering, SYSPRO 6.0, providing an integrated, end-to-end supply chain solution that includes ERP, CRM, APS, E-Commerce, Warehouse Management and Business Analytics.  <br>
<br>
SYSPRO 6.0 is based on Microsoft® .NET architecture and XML standard, SYSPRO e.net solutions forms the foundation of SYSPRO 6.0.   It is a component-based architecture that’s designed to provide a highly cost-effective way for SYSPRO customers to integrate best-of-breed applications, maximize business-to-business trading and leverage wireless connectivity.   It also provides the framework for a new generation of web-based applications. These new applications developed using Microsoft ASP.NET and Microsoft. NET architecture will be fully customizable to meet customer requirements.<br>
<br>
As well as ushering in a new generation of Web Services, SYSPRO 6.0 offers functional and ease of use enhancements to nearly all-existing SYSPRO modules.  <br>
<br>
SYSPRO is one of the world’s most honored software companies. Recent milestones include: The premier K2 Quality Award for “Installation Channel/Methodology” for the SYSPRO STARS Implementation Methodology; Voted Number One in 2002 Middle Market ERP Software Survey Conducted by Accounting Research; Recipient of START Magazine’s First Annual Vision Award (2001) and “Hottest Company” designation for three years; Finalist for Developer of the Year (2002) by Software Council of Southern California; Ranked Among World’s Top Software Companies by MSI Magazine, Managing Automation Magazine, Logistics Management Magazine and Software Magazine; and Given Highest Ratings in Accounting and Manufacturing Software Reviews by CPA Software News for ten consecutive years.<br>
<br>
SYSPRO software is marketed worldwide through offices in the U.S., Canada, Africa, Australia and the U.K. </span></p>
